description: Mundoro Capital Inc., together with its subsidiaries, engages in the investment, acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral resource properties. It primarily explores for gold, copper, silver, and base and precious metal deposits. The company holds a portfolio of properties located in Serbia and Bulgaria. It also has a generative alliance with Vale Exploration Canada Inc. focusing on the generation of new projects to host porphyry copper and related metals deposits within Arizona and New Mexico. In addition, the company owns a 100% interest in the Camargo project, a porphyry copper-gold deposit located in the Southeastern Chihuahua state of Mexico. Mundoro Capital Inc. was incorporated in 2008 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Ms. Teodora  Dechev B.A.Sc., MBA, P.Eng.
